==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Untwine
<hw>Un*twine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>twine</ets>.]</ety> <def>To untwist; to separate,
as that which is twined or twisted; to disentangle; to untie.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It requires a long and powerful counter sympathy in a nation to
<qex>untwine</qex> the ties of custom which bind a people to the
established and the old.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untwine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Untwine
<hw>Un*twine"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become untwined.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untwirl</ent>⟦br⟧
